records.addlTxt: Amended Restitution Order, signed and filed.

Defendant Jason Bickert in court with attorney Julius Kim.  Bruce J. Landgraf appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Sentencing proceeds.  Statements made by the State, defense counsel and defendant. Additional statements made by the victim, K.S.; defendant's mother, Vanette K.; and defendant's wife, Peggy B.

AS TO COUNT 1:    Court sentenced defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT in the Wisconsin State Prisons for 4 YEARS.  
INITIAL CONFINEMENT of 2 YEARS and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 2 YEARS. 
Credit given for ZERO days time served if revoked.

Court finds defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.
Court finds defendant is NOT eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.

COURT STAYS sentence and places defendant on PROBATION for 4 YEARS under the supervision of Wisconsin Department of Corrections.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION/EXTENDED SUPERVISION (AS TO COUNT 1): 
* Comply with the standard rules of probation/extended supervision.
* SERVE 1 YEAR "condition time" at the House of Correction with release priveleges for employment purposes only - STAYED until 07-30-2015 at 12:00 PM.  IF DEFENDANT HAS ANY VIOLATIONS, THE REMAINING CONDITION TIME IS TO CONVERT TO STRAIGHT TIME.
* No contact with the victims.
* Seek and maintain full-time employment.
* Cooperate and participate with an AODA assessment and follow any recommended treatment.
* Cooperate and participate with any other programming deemed appropriate by the Probation Department.
* Provide a DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge - to be paid over a period of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
* PAY the balance of all applicable court costs, fees, and surcharges - to be paid over a period of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
* PAY restitution in the amount of $175,749.70 payable to PAK Technologies, Inc. - to be paid over a period of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.

OTHER COURT ORDERS:
* Court will allow this probation/extended supervision order to transfer to Washington County, if accepted.
* Court finds defendant is NOT eligible for electronic monitoring.
* Court finds defendant is NOT eligible for Good Time Release Credit.
* Court finds defendant does not have illegal drug or alcohol abuse issues, therefore, submitting to random urine screens is not necessary.

  
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm or body armor.  
Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.
Appeal rights given.

Defendant Jason Bickert in court with attorney Julius Kim.  Bruce J. Landgraf appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

AS TO COUNT 1:    Defendant changes plea to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Defendant is advised he is a convicted felon and may not possess any firearms. Defendant is advised he is unable to vote in any election until civil rights are restored. Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.
